# Magmathor

## Setup

### Prerequisites

- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) (Python package manager)

### Installation

```bash
# Install dependencies
uv sync

# Install pre-commit hooks (for code formatting)
uv run pre-commit install
```

> **Note:** The plan generator must be run from WSL.

## Running Model Evaluations

There are two ways to run model evaluations:

### Option 1: Local Testing with `model_tester.py`

Run evaluations locally using the `model_tester.py` script. This is useful for debugging or running on a local GPU.

**Basic usage:**
```bash
python Magmathor/Model/model_tester.py --test <test_name> --model <model_path> --model-name <display_name>
```

**Examples:**

```bash
# Test with the base Qwen2.5-VL model on test_new_positions_1
python Magmathor/Model/model_tester.py \
    --test test_new_positions_1 \
    --model Qwen/Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct \
    --model-name Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct_BASE

# Test a fine-tuned model with custom temperature
python Magmathor/Model/model_tester.py \
    --test test_new_rooms \
    --model /path/to/finetuned/model \
    --model-name MyFinetunedModel \
    --temperature 0.8


# Print results only (no testing)
python Magmathor/Model/model_tester.py \
    --test test_new_positions_1 \
    --print-all-results-auto
```

**Available arguments:**
| Argument | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `--test` | Test set name (e.g., `test_new_positions_1`, `test_new_rooms`) |
| `--model` | Model path or HuggingFace model name |
| `--model-name` | Human-readable name for results display |
| `--temperature` | Sampling temperature (default: 0.6) |
| `--text_only` | Only use text in prompt
| `--print-results` | Print results without running tests |
| `--print-all-results-auto` | Auto-discover and print all results |
| `--check-completion` | Check if all tests are complete (exits with code 0/1) |

### Option 2: Azure ML Testing with AMLT

Run evaluations at scale on Azure ML using AMLT (Azure Machine Learning Tools).

**Prerequisites:**

First, activate the amulet environment:
```powershell
C:/Users/laliden/Code/amulet/venv/Scripts/Activate.ps1
```

**Commands:**

Run evaluation experiment:
```bash
amlt run Magmathor/Model/aml_evaluate.yaml -y {job_name}
```

Collect test results (stores results in blob storage under `/Tests/results.csv`):
```bash
amlt run Magmathor/Model/aml_results.yaml -y {job_name}
```

